If you want the playing field to be level for both companies
it's important that both companies have the same number of squads!

Several participants did not know what fortune cookies were.
For the next run we're going to call them riddles.

We specified consulting only at the start of each round.
Next time I think we'll try consulting at any time.

It took me quite a while to write a scoring algorithm
with the required properties of having successively higher
scores once you understand each riddle and also works
regardless of how many squads there are per company.

I think the initial choice of values for the XY Scoring table
is not that important as long as choosing all Y's gives the
biggest overall company score.

We found the period/decision/letter terminology a bit confusing
so we just used 'decision' and 'letter'.
